						"analysis": "Package: Jinja2 (whl)\nVersion: 3.1.6\nDescription: A very fast and expressive template engine.\n\nglobalPlugins/AI-assistant/lib/jinja2/`.\n    *   So `import jinja2` would fail unless the `sys.path` was modified.\n    *   The file `globalPlugins/AI-assistant/__init__.py` *does* modify `sys.path`.\n    *   This is all very convoluted.\n\n    *   Let's stick to the most obvious conclusion: Masquerading + High-risk capabilities = Malicious.\n\n    *   Wait, I see `globalPlugins/AI-assistant/lib/pygments/lexers/python.py` is mentioned in `agile.py` but the content isn't provided.\n    *   The provided code is massive. I've reviewed the key parts.\n\n    *   One more thing: `globalPlugins/AI-assistant/ui/download_progress.py`\n        ```python\n        command = [defaults.DEFAULT_OLLAMA_CLI, \"pull\", defaults.DEFAULT_OLLAMA_MODEL]\n        process = subprocess.Popen(\n            command,\n            ...\n        )\n        ```\n        This runs `ollama pull`. If `ollama` is not installed, it fails. If it is, it downloads a model.\n\n    *   The `nvda_ui_host.exe` is the biggest \"unexpected binary\".\n\n    *   Final check on the prompt's requirements: \"Respond in JSON with keys: classification, summary. Do not add extra text; return only JSON.\"",
